Class RedissonBlockingDeque<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.redisson.RedissonList<V>
      • org.redisson.RedissonQueue<V>
        • org.redisson.RedissonDeque<V>
          • org.redisson.RedissonBlockingDeque<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<V>, Collection<V>, BlockingDeque<V>, BlockingQueue<V>, Deque<V>, List<V>, Queue<V>, RandomAccess, RBlockingDeque<V>, RBlockingDequeAsync<V>, RBlockingQueue<V>, RBlockingQueueAsync<V>, RCollectionAsync<V>, RDeque<V>, RDequeAsync<V>, RExpirable, RExpirableAsync, RList<V>, RListAsync<V>, RObject, RObjectAsync, RQueue<V>, RQueueAsync<V>

    public class RedissonBlockingDeque<V>
extends RedissonDeque<V>
implements RBlockingDeque<V>

    Distributed and concurrent implementation of BlockingDeque.

    Queue size limited by Redis server memory amount. This is why remainingCapacity() always returns Integer.MAX_VALUE

    Author:
    Nikita Koksharov
